.TH "rdma_get_gid_attr" 9 "rdma_get_gid_attr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rdma_get_gid_attr \- Returns GID attributes for a port of a device at a requested gid_index, if a valid GID entry exists.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const struct ib_gid_attr *" rdma_get_gid_attr
.BI "(struct ib_device *device "  ","
.BI "u8 port_num "  ","
.BI "int index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
The device to query.
.IP "port_num" 12
The port number on the device where the GID value
is to be queried.
.IP "index" 12
Index of the GID table entry whose attributes are to
be queried.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBrdma_get_gid_attr\fP acquires reference count of gid attributes from the
cached GID table. Caller must invoke \fBrdma_put_gid_attr\fP to release
reference to gid attribute regardless of link layer.

Returns pointer to valid gid attribute or ERR_PTR for the appropriate error
code.
